    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras enter April 25 with a lineup optimized for high-upside speed and situational platoon advantages. The standout play of the day is **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (80.98), whose matchup against Roki Sasaki is deceptively favorable; despite his batting order position, the combination of a +19% SP skill boost and an expected 5.52 xERA from Sasaki makes him our premier start. Similarly, **Junior Caminero** (71.50) and **Trea Turner** (70.16) serve as our offensive anchors. **Trea Turner** leverages a prime lead-off spot against Bryce Elder, while **Junior Caminero** benefits from a strong platoon edge and favorable volume, making them the primary drivers for our Runs and RBI projections today.\n\nSeveral players are capitalizing on environmental factors to elevate their status. **Kyle Schwarber** (66.62) remains a locked-in start, bolstered by an elite 0.402 xwOBA and a generous park factor. Meanwhile, **Caleb Durbin** (55.61) receives a significant +16% park adjustment that helps offset a neutral platoon matchup, keeping him in the mix. Conversely, the benching of **Victor Scott II** (38.48) was the most difficult decision of the morning. While his elite speed is highly valued by our front office, a brutal matchup against the arm of Bryan Woo\u2014resulting in a -17% SP skill penalty\u2014dropped him below our 40-point efficiency floor. \n\nRisks remain throughout the card, particularly with \"Lineup Pending\" designations across nearly the entire roster. We are closely monitoring the status of **Dillon Dingler**, **Gary Sanchez**, and **Colt Keith**; should these assume lower-order spots than currently projected, their efficiency scores will likely see downward revisions. Additionally, while we favor the upside of **Hyeseong Kim** (57.38) due to the wind factor, he faces the tactical risk of an elite hold pitcher who stifles stolen base attempts. We will continue to hold **Christian Yelich** on the IL and monitor **Carson Benge** following his postponement, maintaining roster flexibility while we wait for official lineups to lock.",
